Paper: hep-th/9409106

Date: 1994-09-19

Title: Deformed Poincare Algebra and Field Theory

Authors: Alexandros A. Kehagias, Patrick A.A. Meessen and George Zoupanos

Comments: 14 pages, LATEX, prep. MPI-Ph/94-58

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B346 (1995) 262-268

We examine deformed Poincar\'e algebras containing the exact Lorentz algebra.We impose constraints which are necessary for defining field theories on thesealgebras and we present simple field theoretical examples. Of particularinterest is a case that exhibits improved renormalization properties.